PARABOLA

DE SEMINATORE scoth.

EHALD, ene sawer gaed furth til saw.

An’ when he sawet, some seeds fell hie the waye-side‚ en' the fowlis 0' the eir eem’ en’ gorblet them up.

Sume fell upon stanie pleeeS, where they hadne meikle yird: an’ at enee they spreng up, beeaus they had nee deepniss 0’ yird:

An’ when the sun was up, they wer seowderet3 an’ beeaus they had nae rute they wutheret awa.

An’ sume fell emang thorns3 an' the thorns sprang up, en’ choket them.

But ithers ’ fell intill guid grum an’ broueht furth hut, sume ane hundret-

fauld‚ sume saxty·fauld, sume thretty· fauld.

Wha heth ears til hear, let him hear.
